title: Volleyball roundup: Huntsmen stun Shermans
text:
Volleyball roundup: Huntsmen stun Shermans Gazette Staff 10:18 p.m. EDT September 29, 2015 1 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Chillicothe 3, East Clinton 0 
With a sweep of East Clinton; 25-9, 25-12 and 25-15; the Chillicothe Cavaliers stayed on top of the South Central Ohio League, Tuesday night. 
Malia Berry had another good night with nine kills and five blocks and got help from Gabby Lapurga who dished out 21 assists and added five aces. Maris Corzine led the team in digs with seven while Olivia Eblin added nine kills. 
The Cavaliers (11-7, 9-1 SCOL) will return to the court at home on Thursday, against Clinton-Massie. 
Huntington 3, Unioto 2 
In a battle within the SVC’s top three teams, Huntington came away with a five-set win over Unioto at home, Thursday night; 20-25, 25-23, 14-25, 25-23 and 15-11. 
Huntington’s Dylana Gragg had a career night with 38 kills, 18 digs, four blocks, and nine assists. Following that terrific effort was Rikki Magill with 13 kills, two aces, 22 digs and 22 assists. Kennedy DeBord chipped in with five kills, 10 digs, an ace, two blocks and 14 assists while Carolane Cox registered five kills, 20 digs, a block and three assists. 
For Unioto, senior Kassidey Winegardner led the way with 15 kills, 22 digs and three aces while her younger sister, Abbey, posted 13 kills, an ace, 14 digs and two assists. 
Huntington (13-3, 7-2 SVC) will play again Thursday, at home, against Zane Trace. Unioto (15-2, 7-2 SVC) returns Thursday as well, at home against Westfall. 
Westfall 3, Paint Valley 0 
After a successful weekend, Westfall continued its hot streak with a sweep of Paint Valley, Tuesday night; 25-21, 25-17 and 25-17. 
The Mustangs were led by Hannah Phillips, who posted 15 kills, 25 digs and 14 assists. Becca Brown also chipped in with 15 digs while Darby Beavers added 18 assists. 
For Paint Valley, Lea McFadden led the charge with 18 digs, six kills and an ace. Madison Smith also helped out with six digs, six assists, three aces and two kills. 
Westfall (9-5, 6-3 SVC) will now travel to Unioto, Thursday, while Paint Valley (4-10, 0-9 SVC) hosts Piketon the same evening. 
Adena 3, Piketon 0 
The Adena Warriors continued to roll inside SVC play with a sweep of Piketon, Tuesday night; 25-17, 25-17 and 25-20. 
Devon Putnam led the Warriors with 16 kills, eight digs and two aces while Carissa Poehler added 16 kills as well. Also appearing on the Warriors’ stat sheet was Lanie Shea with 37 assists and 12 digs as well as Carly Carroll with 16 digs. 
For Piketon, Cami Chandler led the ‘Streaks in kills with 11 while Jordan Morris added nine kills and 20 digs. Maci Conley had 12 assists while Payton Reuter added nine. 
Adena (15-2, 9-0 SVC) will now travel to Southeastern, Thursday, while Piketon (8-9, 1-8 SVC) makes a trip to Paint Valley. 
Waverly 3, Oak Hill 0 
Staying atop the Southern Ohio Conference Tuesday night was the Waverly Tigers with a sweep of Oak Hill; 25-9, 25-12 and 25-9. 
The Tigers were led by Jaimee Stewart with 11 kills and got offensive aid from Maddy Wiseman in the form of 30 assists. Wiseman finished with seven digs and Kalynn Baker had 11 points from the service line. 
Waverly (12-3, 9-0 SOC) will host South Webster, Thursday night. 1 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1FCtAnr TOP VIDEOS
